# EvolveX — Cursor AI Context

## Project
Self-modifying agent evolution system for the EvolveX hackathon.
Agents analyze their own performance, propose code mutations, validate in sandbox, and apply successful changes.

## Stack
- Python 3.13 + FastAPI — agent engine, evolution loop, sandbox execution
- Next.js (App Router) + Tailwind — real-time evolution dashboard
- OpenAI API (Codex / GPT-4.1) — agent intelligence layer
- WebSockets — live dashboard updates

## Architecture
agents/
  base_agent.py       — Base agent class with benchmark + self-analysis
  performer.py        — Agent A: executes benchmark tasks
  analyzer.py         — Agent B: measures performance, identifies improvements
  modifier.py         — Agent C: proposes and applies code mutations

evolution/
  sandbox.py          — Isolated code execution environment
  checkpoint.py       — Save/restore agent states
  fitness.py          — Performance scoring and metrics
  loop.py             — Main evolution orchestrator

dashboard/            — Next.js real-time visualization
  src/app/            — App Router pages
  src/components/     — React components (EvolutionTree, MetricsChart, etc.)
  src/lib/            — WebSocket client, API helpers

## Key Patterns
- Agents NEVER modify themselves directly — all mutations go through sandbox.py first
- Every modification creates a checkpoint before applying
- Failed mutations auto-rollback to last checkpoint
- Fitness scores are the single source of truth for evolution decisions

## Do NOT
- Hardcode API keys — use .env
- Skip sandbox validation — all code runs in isolation first
- Skip checkpoint before mutation — rollback depends on it

## Available Skills (reference with @)
- .agent/skills/multi-agent-patterns — orchestrator/swarm/hierarchical patterns, handoff protocols
- .agent/skills/prompt-engineering — few-shot, chain-of-thought, system prompt design
- .agent/skills/context-engineering — context window management, compression, memory tiers
- .agent/skills/systematic-debugging — root cause tracing, defense-in-depth debugging

## MCP Servers (configured in .cursor/mcp.json)
- context7 — live library docs (use for OpenAI API, FastAPI, Next.js questions)
- brave-search — web search during development
- github — git operations
- playwright / chrome-devtools — dashboard testing
- shadcn — component lookups

## Hackathon Constraints
- This is a time-boxed build. Prefer simple, working code over elegant abstractions.
- Demo readiness matters: every feature must be visible in the dashboard feed.
- The evolution loop emits events — any new behavior must yield an event dict.
- No classes unless necessary (Python). Functions over methods.
- venv is at .venv/ (Python 3.13). Run: source .venv/bin/activate

## Running Locally
# Terminal 1 — backend
source .venv/bin/activate && uvicorn api:app --reload --port 8000

# Terminal 2 — dashboard
cd dashboard && npm run dev
# → http://localhost:3000
